headline.main: Pujara, Rahane Keep India Afloat in Second Test
headline.print_headline: Pujara, Rahane Keep India Afloat in Second Test

lead_paragraph: Cheteshwar Pujara and Ajinkya Rahane shared an unbroken fifth-wicket stand of 93 to keep alive India's hopes of a series-levelling win over Australia, giving the hosts a lead of 126 on a see-saw third day of the second test on Monday.
